#DESCRIPTION#
is used to compress/decompress and archive files
#FORMAT/EXAMPLE#
tar [options] [archivename] [filename]
tar -xjvf bzip_archive.tbz -C /extract_here/
#OPTIONS#
-c : specifies create archive mode
-C : changes to directory name before operation
-x : specifies extract mode
-f : precedes the archive file name
-z : also compresses/decompresses the archive using gzip
-j : also compresses/decompresses the archive using bzip2
-t : lists the files in an archive
-v : verbose output
#END#
